rComments: Very helpful and thoughtful professor. He looks out for the best interest of his students! Highly recommend his course.

Professor Marshall is amazing, he is by far the most helpful professor I have encountered at the University of Toronto. If any students claim that his class is easy is it because Professor Marshall is extremely helpful. He will sit down with you and reiterate concepts during office hours until you understand what he meant. Take this class!

very helpful and willing to answer questions both during and after class. tries to engage students more in the course. allows you to chose your essay topic and posts notes online that better clarify the lecture and textbook. very nice and offers kind advice.

He's very passionate about what he teaches, which helps keep students engaged. He's very kind to students and he posts notes online to help guide our studying :) He gives you the freedom to pick any topic on the main essay and if you ask him for advice he can provide some really valuable insight that really helps :) I'd definitely recommend him! :D
Extremely easy course only if you listen to the prof and his lectures are interesting. and he is always available for help.
